data.title: SHIVAJI
data.text:
First scene of Sivaji!!

http://rajinifans.com/showurl.asp?url=http://sivajimovie.blogspot.com/2005/10/first-scene-of-sivaji.html

Here's some Sivaji news which came in media this evening.

1) Shankar, has recorded all the discussions of Sivaji creation

team, (which he had with his assistants) in a tape and has sent to

Sujatha to write the screen play.

2) According to the script, first scene of the Sivaji starts in a

prison. (Summa nacchunu irukka?)

3) Shankar has banned outgoing calls from the mobiles of his

assistants. Only important incoming calls can be attended. He has

also presented all of them a brand new bike and gave them a sweet

surprise.

Tail Piece:

Superstar, also consults with P Vasu regarding the script of Sivaji,

to add a few commercial elements. P Vasu is said to suggest a few

things. And that in turn, submitted to Shankar with final approval

from Superstar.

Note: All of the news said by me is just for information. And it

doesn't ensure commerial success or viability of a movie. I am very

much particular about the hype and I am maximum refrain from giving

some sort of news which may create hype. Finally, the story and

screenplay and it's presentation alone can give a super duper hit

like Chandramukhi. Let's expect the best.

Sundar.

Special Correspondent hons

prashanth12 wrote: No problem....i just hope people wouldn't equate criticism or objectivity with hating ARR...I'm listening to Mettu Podu as I type this

Prasanth,

I have seen enough criticism against ARR for his albums like parasuram, udhaya, baba, kadhal virus, E20U18 (past 2000 releases) on his acceptance of such dud films is quite acceptable when compared to his hindi & intl ventures(Meenaxi,Bose,Swades,Lagaan,TOBS, WOHE...). I would rank E20U18 & Udhaya, Baba as good for few songs but not GREAT. Whereas Boys, KKS or AE are truly masterpieces with its youthful (Boys), stunning romantic melodies (KKS) & technos (fanaah),folkish song (AE). If you need I can post several reivews which proves (technically) those are GREAT albums.

I would have appreciated if you could post some technical flaws to disprove the greatness of the above said albums rather providing objective advices... DUET's Mettu podu is truly awesome and I alwayss make it sure that I listen to these GEMS frequently.

P.S: Baba's kichu thaa has become one of my all-time fav when i heard it in the hindi version of SWADES/DESAM. Tamil version sucks bcoz of the lyrics. I have also read that there were diff guitars (8 ) used in that song and the use of TT ball pitching is brilliant enough. Can anyone think of such experimenting in a romantic duet or even attempt when you are parallely woking with other hindi & intl albums?

Read the following blog which shows how ARR experiments & I am proud to be his fan who has the guts to do it really worth most of the time

http://arrahmaniac.blogspot.com/2006/02/i-met-sivamani.html If ARR has been so so good. Why did Shankar go to HJ?

HJ to me rates way better than ARR. What do you mean by cut and paste. ARR does that a lottttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttt. He copies tunes left and right from old songs (e.g., Roja Roja from a Hindi song in Varumaiyin Niram Sivappu). People got captivated in his fresh approach in 92. As I said, at that time it touched peoples ears and not hearts (barring a few songs, I can provide you a list). Within 10 years he sounded repititive and boring. That's because his fundamentals were not right. Here are some songs that really touched my heart

1) Uyire Uyire

2) Puthu Vellai Mazhai

3) Anbe.. Anbe (although copied from a western beat)

4) Dilse Re (from Dilse)

5) Malargale Malargale

4) Naan Paadum Sandham

5) Nila Kaigirath

6) Nara Mughaye

7) Thee Thee,

8) Fanaah - The only one since 2000

9) Pachai Nirame

10) Kannamuchi Yennada

11) Yenge Yenadhu Kavidhai

12) Kandukondean KanduKondean

May be a handful more...

Regardinng Dipu Dipu Vs Devuda, I do not want to argue. Both songs sound mediocre and rubbish. I do not see any greatness in them.

But Ra Ra and Kuku Para Para sound okay to me and the entire tamil population received them very well. Baba songs were not received that well. Common, Baba Kichu Kichu tha...sounds like a nursery rhyme. Call it great...something wrong.

Further the problem with ARR these days is that I am not captivated to listen the whole song for some reason. Even Mayil Irage song, the pallavi sounds nice but I soon switch to the next song. The credit goes to SJ Surya for good picturization. Else, the song would have been another mediocre from ARR.

I cannot stand any of ARR songs from E18U20. I tried. Sorry. So is the case with Ayutha Ezhuthu (except Fannah).

FYI, I had interviewed Bhardwaj in Dec 2004 and he volunterly said that ARR is at his worst these days. Doesn't mean much, but same minds think alike. If ARR has been so so good. Why did Shankar go to HJ?

Remember me?

I Came up with the news about songs of Baba & Chandramukhi long before the songs were released. Now I would like to give you asong that I heard from Shivaji. Three songs have been recorded so far. Rajni's intro song is different this time. It is going to be a kind of Rap.

The song that I heard goes like this. It is a duet.

" Poovaambaai...

aambal aambal.

Punnagayo

mavval mavval. "

The tune was mindblowing guys. I think some new voice. But this song, I am sure is going to rock TFM for a long time like narumugaye did. Not much of Rajni in the song.

My friend had heard the Rap song and she told me that it was very catchy. The song happens as a welcome song for Rajni when he returns from America.

There is another melody in the movie by Unni Krishnan. Will try to get some info about that and get back to you later.

Cheers,

dont have high hopes on shivaji from Shankar's ability... I think he has run out of steam and relies only on his reputation like soo many other directors who are not willing to let go.... Shankar.. thinks clever but for how long can he grind the same stuff ... He is obsessed with grand scale of things.. gentleman and mudalvan to an extent are the few good movies to mention .. other than that .. I really have to think hard...

speaking of his movies with a social cause.. 'Thambi' for me conveyed more emotions of a social cause than all his movies put together..... you dont need a mega budget to convey a social message.. I think Shivaji will make him or break him.... Rajni factor will bail him out this time.. but next time??

digression : Btw .. watched 'Chitram pesuthadi ' yesterday .. I can safely comment its the best BGM i have heard this year or even last year...that includes the movies of the Maestros as well... great job by sundar... compelling watch ...

as for shivaji and shankar... shankar please dont pull this one on rajni ... please.... m_23_bayarea

introducing MPD concept alone .. doesnt necessarily mean that shakar is full of ideas.. Shankar is a very creative director..Look what he did to gentleman .. and then kadhalan.. the strength of these movies is shankar..

like RGV getting stuck with underworld movies .. shankar is becoming slotted.. can he come out of it and give a movie other than corruption and social empathy??.. he tried to do things diff in BOYZ... but alas the thrashing (deservedly) he recieved from all sides.. he went back to his tried and tested formula... this time with MPD but that doesnt mean creativity...

take mudhalvan for ex.. . he thought aloud of how one man can change a system and provided a grippy narrative...

I am only worried that in his quest for grandiosity shakar is loosing what made him a 'grand' director...

as said said earlier.. directors like Miskin.(boy this guy was smashing in CP).ameer..selva..murugadas..bala..lingu... hold a lot of promise.. lets see if they would take tfm to the next level..

Spain Naathil 'Sivaji' Paadhal

Here it goes Dinesh,

If its a Rajini film then the first song would be recorded by SPB. This has been the trend so far. This includes Annamali, Arunachalma, Padayappa, Baba and Chandramukhi. For sivaji who has sung the first song is not still clear, but 3 songs have been recorded by 'Isai Puyal' A R Rahman.

For Sivaji Hariharan has recorded one song out of the 3. Is this the 1st song? It is not clear, but what is clear is that Shankar has planned to film 2 out of the 3 songs in Spain.

25 dancers from a famous 'Ballet' group in london are expected to dance for this song along with Rajini and Shreya.

Prabudheva is to Choreograph these songs while K.V Anand handles the camera. Both are expected to leave on 18th MAy for Spain.

Rajini, Sreya and Shankar will leave on 20th to Spain where they will spend about 1 week filming the song and will return this month end. Sivaji songs unveiled

Eager to hear some news about Superstars Sivaji songs? Dont you worry folks. We have got news. Reliable, first hand, and scoop. What more can you ask for? Credible sources revealed that Sivaji has 7 songs to its credit. All being pep songs with energetic beats from Rahman, they are sure to propel the movies music in the top position for a long time.

Out of the seven songs from Sivaji, we have got news about 5 numbers.

Va ji, Va ji, Sivaji

This could be the opening song of the movie. Though it was decided earlier not to have Rajinis entry into the movie with an introductory song, Shankar is contemplating with the thought of reinstating one such song. That could be it.

Unpeyar ennada

As is the rule in Rajinis movies, we presume that this is a philosophical number joining the likes of other famous songs of the same genre, which are quintessential for his movies.

Boom boom jee boom ba

This most likely is the duet song with Shreya and Rajini in the lead. If that is true Rajini could be seen shaking his legs with Shreya either in the exotic European locations or simply in our neighbouring Karnataka.

Talla dimi takka dimi pucha..pyun pyun enna rastina..ho ra ho yenna rastina.. hoo haa..

Didnt decipher a word of it, dont you worry or be concerned about the plight of Tamil lyrics in songs. This song is Japanese and will be shot in Japan when the next schedule commences.

Adaal udan pesadha di.. en salangai ku bhadil solladi..

You might wonder what the old Vanjikottai Valiban song is doing in Sivajis song list. We assume that inspired by the hits the remix of old songs generate, Shankar has decided to embrace one such song. This song could be a climax song or just like the one in Padayappa where Ramyakrishnan challenges Rajini with her dance moves, but with the lead ladies.

Stay tuned for more updates and we will enlighten you with more news when our reliable birdie coos news into our ears. Ciao.

http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-04/11-10-06-sivaji.html Vairamuthu Show in Muscat & Sivaji News

http://sivajimovie.blogspot.com/

(From the article)

Vairamuthu in his speech talked about his entry to films, his association with Barathiraja, Illayaraja, MSV, KB, Maniratnam, Kamal and at last about Annan in Sivaji. He was very emotional and with a distinct loud and confident voice said QUOTE : "Sivaji will create history in Tamil cinema with regards to quality, collections and substance. Sivaji will be the greatest achievement for superstar Rajini and will be talked by people till Tamil cinema exists" UNQUOTE. He went on to narrate that QUOTE : "director Shankar asked for a love song and after several revisions spread over 2 months, the song was ready. The shoot was in Hyd. in a specially erected set of mirrors costing 2.5 crores. After the shoot was completed, Shankar called vairamuthu and requested him to change the song as the song lyrics did not match the mirror set erected. Vairamuthu rewote the song and the song was reshot. Such is the committment and detail to which Director Shankar is working for this movie. He asked the crowd to listen to this song after the audio release and confidently declared that this song will conquer each and every music lover in the world" Vairamuthu Show in Muscat & Sivaji News

The audio of much awaited Shivaji will be launched on March 20, sources of AVM studios confirmed unofficially. However Director Shankar is giving his final touches to the Trailer of the film and the same will be released in a day or two. Sources revealed that the trailer will be released only in theaters first and would later be telecast on television channels and the Internet. When we approached the producers AVM Saravanan and MS Guhan, they maintained a strict silence about the movie. But MS Guhan hinted that the audio release might be in the last week of March after the release of its trailer. But there is no response from the director.

This is the main reason why so little is known about the movie and its release. It is widely beleived tha he intends to raise hypw about the film by keeping his silence. There are 16 theaters which are staking their claims to screen Shivaji in the City. Among them Inox, Sathyam, Mayajal, Abirami, Udayam, Brinda, Albert, Bharat and Rohini complexes are already confirmed to screen Shivaji, Apart from this, there are more than 40 theaters queued for the same from the outskirts. The premiere of the movie would be held in Sthyam Theatre and Inox, a day before the release of the film.

All the ratings are IMHO....

1) Ore Oru Suriyan Pole - 4:48 (SPB, Blaaze) = 8/10

This is the intro song for Rajni. The unique instrumentation at the beginning is very catchy. The mass + class will enjoy this. The kids voice in the saranam is very apt, the voice sounds like the boy from Yeh Tara (but no credits though!) The final punch is the 2 liner from Super Star himself at the end with that drum beats that we have never heard before!..... Super Stars are back! (ARR + Rajni)

2) Un Vizhigalil - 5:30 (Unni Krishnan, Shreya Goshal) = 9.5/10

One of the most hummable tune of the year! The tune instantly sticks to your mind. In fact the interlude is repeated softly in Grahana Tinggal song. The overlapping of Unni Krishnan and Shreya's line was great and shows the best of ARR!

3) Grahana Tinggal - 4:24 (Karthik) = 8.5/10

A rustic, and sad song. Probably featured when Rajni's character is going through a rough patch. Karthik simply gave his best in this song. The energy was evident in his voice, while the backing does what it suppose to do, TO BE AT THE BACK!. The interlude is great, as ARR used the smae interlude from Un Vizhigalil (slower tempo) with added separate tune played in Maestro's old pal, PAN FLUTE!

4) Chor Chor - 5:49 (Tippu, Harini, Sujatha, Febi & MSV) = 9.8/10

This is a group event song I believe. All the voices are wonderful, perfect extraction from ARR. MSV's rustic rendition of 2 liners every now and then are awesome. It just shows the depth of imagination of ARR. This song will be played in all weddings, birthday and major functions after this. Basically the song is lead by Tippu & Harini with the others teases them throughout the song. It starts with Hindi Chor Chor and it stops with hindi there. Wonderful lyrics by Vaali!

5) Instrumental of Grahana Tinggal - 2:34 = 8/10

The instrumental sounds really good, but this time the backing that took the back stage comes forward as a result, you get heavy beats! The mandolin like sounds throughtout the song is really haunting!

6) Tittam ittupaar - 4: 36 (ARR) = 10/10

Whats a Rajni movie without motivational song. You ask for it, and you get the best from Maestro! 'Tittam ittupaar, atthai vattam ittupaar' has some good lyrics and it's really sounds good and sticks to you. It is best comparable with Vazhkaiyil 1000 tadaikal from Padayappa

7) Theme Music - 2:12

Awesome! the beat, tempo, raaga(softly added only comes forward with good stereo sounds system though!) and its couple of verses of Sanskrit! WOW WOW WOW!.....

Overal, the album is sure chartbuster! i would give it a 9/10 as an album rating. Even when I am writing this review I have already heard the songs being aired on OLI (Singapore radio!).... Possible Future Reviews :

Karthik,

Inspections are on how it has leaked But we are sure that it has come out from the sets. All the songs are scratches The final mixing is nowhere near to these.

Esplly on the Sunlight song sung by Shaggy, Blaaze and Tanvi; what is available on net is just a scratch piece for shooting. And Sahana song is sung A.R himself on the final version with Chinmayi. We have one more brilliant number called Day light dude which is the opening song sung by Rappers from US.

We have a Song recorded with the voice of Rajinikanth Sir and Drums kit played by Siva Sir which is interesting, in the movie. Please dont post your opinions and underestimate the soundtrack now it now. Its does enhance the visuals on screen quite brilliantly and wait for the moment to catch it on 70 mm.

I was actually refraining myself from posting till the final version is out, But I guess some things are never going to change in them.

Before I even venture into the songs part, let me throw my views on RK. I am not an RK fanatic nor anybody's. But I do know after living in India and abroad that RK's movies are no longer percieved as just movies. For any tamil, each passing day before release is like expecting a harvest, a festival. Somehow TN people have showered him with the greatest affection only second to MGR. I will not bow down my head in shame if I said RK is THE definition of a superstar. No not even AB can match him.

For tamil folks watching his movies is like a festival in town and the urge to be a part of it. I see this happening ever since Baasha days. The funny thing is you dont look for complex themes. You just need RK and lots of him.

Every album of RK is bound to be a superhit irrespective of who the MD is. And the best part is every tamil expects to lipsync his songs in one form or the other. Lets not venture in the past, just take CM for ex. It could be the mediocre "Annonoda Paatu"/"Devuda" .. or the super "Ra rA". Fans all over the world/ folks sitting at the tea shops/ kids front of the TV ..want to sing with him. You dont need complexity.

Vaa Ji ..Shivaji ... Medicore composition .. just about right for RK movie. Bound to be a super hit... fans will rejoice...

Saahana.. the best so far. its a kind of growing melody. but for a RK movie????? I dont think fans want to lap up RK as a hopeless romantic... there is no peppiness in the song whatsoever.... Probably after a long time "Dum" break is also possible in an RK movie.

"Sunlight Moonlight" or whatever ... by composing this ..Shankar and team has robbed scores of fans an opportunity to mouth his lines.. this song will never go beyond the movie run. I am now doubly worried about another "Daylight dude" ... what are they tryng to get at ???

and the choice of singers??? lyrics ...??? RK-ARR-SHANKAR-VM comes up with " Pengalidam solvathu kuraivu ..Seivathu Athigam ..Seyal Veeran Nanadi"" ??? is this all you can come up with ??? For the choice of singers ARR and shankar has to take equal blame. The pronounciations are preposterous. Ironically there are lines of "Nan Pacchi tamilan " .. when the same lines are mouthed by some unknown guy who cant speak a word of it .... what was VM doing during recording when his lines were killed ??? is it the same guy who wrote " Thangame Tamizhukillai Thattupadu" ?? Shame on you VM for letting them kill Tamil.

Even its a reggae... show us ur creativity

And as somebody mentioned earlier, I pray that 3 songs presented are the bottom of the pile because it doesnt show an year's worthof effort and painfully pray that the songs are sung by somebody else. I listened to the new additions along with the 3 old ones. Overall, there isnt a single song that is going to stay with me for more than a week or two. Not surprising, since its a Shankar movie and a Rajni-starrer on top of that. They go for immediate appeal.

Amongst the songs the ones that make some sort of impression on first listening are "Style"(although it would have been better placed in a movie like Boys), portions of "Athiradee"(although wasnt too impressed with the tune) and portions of "Boss"(the wind instrument tone used in the BGM sounds pretty cool)

Was not too impressed with the rest.

Sahana seems to be a peppier waltzier update of "porkaLam inge"(Tenali), although with some pretty neat mrudhangam usage. I didnt find anything special in the tune. Certainly not in the league of "Munbe vaa" but since its a Tajni film the song might pick up after constant replays on TV.

Vaaji-medicore tune, nothing special.

Balleilakka - SPB rocks, defying the age factor. Take him away, nothing much left.

I got the impression that they wanted to have a mass feel yet come out with something different and worked too hard on that aspect. But the thing is that some of the songs end up being neither here nor there.
